female commanding
officer of her JROTC unit at
Alonzo and Tracy

50:25.956 --> 50:30.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mourning Senior High in Miami.
Her story caps
off a week of coverage from our
Student Reporting

50:30.661 --> 50:36.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Labs on redefining gender in our
society.
It's part of our Outside the Box
series.

50:36.500 --> 50:40.170 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Fall out. Attention.
Right-face.

50:40.271 --> 50:49.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHANTELL GONZALEZ, Student: My
name is Shantell
Gonzalez. I'm the C.O. of the
NJROTC program

50:49.980 --> 50:55.653 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
here at Alonzo and Tracy
Mourning. C.O. represents
commanding officer, who is in
charge of the

50:55.753 --> 50:57.521 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
entire company.

50:57.621 --> 51:00.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: Being a woman in a
male-dominated
military branch comes with
several struggles

51:00.624 --> 51:04.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and conquests. But Shantell
Gonzalez has never
let that come between her and
her passion

51:05.029 --> 51:06.864 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for serving.

51:06.964 --> 51:09.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHANTELL GONZALEZ: Difficult
being a female
and leading -- trying to lead
males, especially

51:09.166 --> 51:13.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
your age group, because cadets
don't think
that they should be being told
what to do

51:13.304 --> 51:17.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by a person in general, and then
being told
what to do by a female is even
harder for

51:17.908 --> 51:19.743 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
them to listen.

51:19.843 --> 51:24.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they will eventually -- if
you do it the
correct way, they will
eventually follow what

51:24.148 --> 51:25.983 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you will say.

51:26.083 --> 51:29.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: In order to keep up
with the demands
of being a commanding officer,
Shantell attends

51:29.553 --> 51:32.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a physical training course with
current and
former Marines.

51:32.656 --> 51:36.994 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Staff Sergeant David Castro
(ph), an active-duty
Marine Corps recruiter who
mentors young cadets

51:37.094 --> 51:41.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
at the Miami school, says
Shantell not only
far exceeds the expectations of
others, but

51:42.066 --> 51:44.068 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
also the expectations she has of
herself.

51:44.168 --> 51:47.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STAFF SGT. DAVID CASTRO, Marine
Corps: She
comes here every day with a lot
of enthusiasm.

51:47.504 --> 51:53.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's very optimistic about her
future. And
she's here to compete. And it
shows on a daily

51:53.310 --> 51:58.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
basis every time she come here.
Sometimes,
she's put some of our guys to
shame.

51:58.682 --> 52:04.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: I see her working out,
pushing herself
more. And when I see her do, it
makes me want

52:04.822 --> 52:06.724 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to push myself.

52:06.824 --> 52:09.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHANTELL GONZALEZ: How do you
think men get
up to where they are? They work
for it. Females

52:09.326 --> 52:11.128 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
